The paper deals with multi-terminal source coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves side information, which is a common theme in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of cost-constrained actions suggests a connection to optimization and decision making (cs.DS), and the characterization of trade-offs is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG).
